text.__SUMMARY__: Prunus odorata is a species of plant in the family Rosaceae. It is endemic to Peninsular Malaysia. It is threatened by habitat loss. Some sources treat it as a synonym of Prunus mahaleb.
text.References: Chua, L.S.L. (1998). "Prunus odorata". The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. IUCN. 1998: e.T31778A9653205. doi:10.2305/IUCN.UK.1998.RLTS.T31778A9653205.en. Retrieved 18 December 2017.
